{"id":"JUDGE-1","rule_id":"spec.max-runs-no-extra-execution","severity":"HIGH","file":"schedule/__init__.py","line":713,"message":"If job_func raises on the nth invocation, control never reaches the budget cancellation check, so Scheduler._run_job receives no CancelJob and leaves the job scheduled. A subsequent run invokes job_func again; the behavioral probe produced two calls, scheduler membership true, and _remaining_runs == -1 for max_runs(1), violating self-removal and the requirement that an (n+1)-th execution never happen.","quote":"ret = self.job_func()\n        self.last_run = datetime.datetime.now()\n        self._schedule_next_run()\n\n        if self._remaining_runs is not None and self._remaining_runs <= 0:\n            logger.debug(\"Cancelling job %s\", self)\n            return CancelJob","confidence":"high"}
